posts.cooked:
Hey programing cd I am back once again with a little debacle, I implemented some pose estimation code and now when I try to deploy my code to the rio it just crashes. I have tried to comment out the code that uses path planer auto builder and it was still crashing, Then out of a bit of frustration I commented out the auto builder in container and it deployed.

In the logs I get this message ﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ERROR ﻿﻿ 1 ﻿﻿ The robot program quit unexpectedly. This is usually due to a code error.   The above stacktrace can help determine where the error occurred.   See https://wpilib.org/stacktrace for more information.  ﻿﻿ edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:383) ﻿﻿﻿ ﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ 	at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:370) ﻿ ﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ 	at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.startRobot(RobotBase.java:510) ﻿ ﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ 	at frc.robot.Main.main(Main.java:13) ﻿ ﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿  ﻿ ﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ Error at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:383): The robot program quit unexpectedly. This is usually due to a code error. ﻿ ﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ERROR ﻿﻿ 1 ﻿﻿ Could not instantiate robot com.pathplanner.lib.auto.AutoBuilder! ﻿﻿ edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:389) ﻿﻿﻿

and here is my code 2025-guppy-Reefscape/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/CommandSwerveDrivetrain.java at main · Team3039/2025-guppy-Reefscape · GitHub

Thanks a bunch for the help in advanced .

Do you have the error message of configuring AutoBuilder deploy failing?

no but I do get this error

Because AutoBuilder is not configured. You have to configure AutoBuilder. But you said they were issues configuring AutoBuilder

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked:
I looked at your code and I see you’re using a CTRE swerve. This actually has pose estimation built in, so you shouldn’t need to create your own pose estimator. In your vision code, you should just call CommandSwerveDrivetrain.addVisionMeasurement with your resulting measurement.

You’re already feeding the values from CTRE ’s pose estimator into PathPlanner, which is correct: image 1155×601 77.7 KB

image 1155×601 77.7 KB

image 1155×601 77.7 KB

Can you provide a bit more info on the problem you’re seeing? I pulled your code and it starts up fine in the sim.

You removed the Telemetry class and commented out the sim code in CommandSwerveDrivetrain , but when I add those back I can even see the robot driving in the sim during auto.

posts.name: Miles.D
posts.cooked:
Ok I just pushed my code the problem I am still running into is

I changed around the auto builder but its still is giving this error am I just misplacing it in the code?

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked:
You commented out the code in CommandSwerveDrivetrain ’s constructor that was calling configureAutoBuilder() , so like the message says, AutoBuilder was not configured. Uncomment the call.

Also, inside configureAutoBuilder() , you have a call back to itself . This will cause the robot to hang and eventually crash with a stack overflow exception because it just keeps calling itself. Just remove it.

posts.name: Sam Bowling
posts.cooked: You need to be calling configureAutoBuilder() in every constructor for CommandSwerveDrivetrain . We also did CTRE , and one of the only differences I could tell from our code , was that you had those calls commented out and we didn’t.

posts.name: Miles.D
posts.cooked: Ok thank you very much I got it working

posts.cooked: Thank you your code was a very big help
